snippet.textDisplay:
As a Chinese citizen I would like to point out some of the discrepancies in the information that people outside of China may receive. Please share this out so that the world understands how this regime works.


1. The virus was quite thoroughly analysed and reported by mid-December, 2019. While the Chinese Communist Party are trying to gear public anger towards the Wuhan local government for not reporting, the scientists for hiding information in order to publish academic papers, and the citizens of Wuhan for their "outrageously savage-like" diet, evidence (including interviews and data-tracking) has shown that the local government did report the cases but had to wait for the Central Government's order before releasing any information, and that the delay in information release was, according to CCP traditions, very likely in order to create a "harmonious media coverage" on a recent major political conference (8 doctors were arrested and detained for warning people of "a contagious SARS outbreak in Wuhan", one of them now at the brink of death due to the disease). The subsequent delay in information release was instead to create a "harmonious atmosphere" for the coming Lunar New Year, which is culturally and politically an important festival of the country.


2. The number of death and number of infected are SEVERELY UNDERREPORTED. While the reports were delayed and the numbers hampered due to typical CCP politics, a clear comparison with other disasters within China could provide hint on the extent of this event. Take the Tianjin explosions in 2015 as an example, the explosion equivalent to 336 tons of TNT blew up an entire port, bore a crater into the city, killed 173 people, and created a chemical rain on top of the entire region. However, Tianjin did not stop functioning for a SINGLE DAY. This time the Chinese government is shutting down cities after cities, and even "proudly stating" that "the crematorium is open 24/7, serving citizens more with greater efficiency than usual" (this is not a joke, it is an actual official post by the Chinese propaganda). At this point, the numbers are underreported NOT ONLY due to political concerns, but also because of the
lack of testing kits and medical resources. Patients simply die before getting diagnosed, and they DO NOT count towards either the infected numbers or the death counts. Hospital all so overloaded they simply ask people to leave and go back home for quarantine. Numerous video shows that people are dying right on the streets. Of course, you can call these misinformation as you like, but as a Chinese citizen that knows how the CCP works, we know it's not something to be taken this lightly of. Ask someone who has lived in the Soviet Union and they might enlighten you on how bureaucratic authoritarian regimes like this work.


Feel free to ask questions, and if I happen to still be around and saw a worthwhile question, I might answer it in detail.
Stay safe, and stay healthy in the Year of the Rat.
